    <p>MI­LAN • Euro­pean foot­ball clubs could lose an es­ti­mated €5.2 bil­lion to €6.3 bil­lion (S$10 bil­lion) in rev­enues due to the im­pact of the Covid-19 pan­demic, Euro­pean Club As­so­ci­a­tion chair­man An­drea Agnelli said on Thurs­day.</p>
    <p>Fi­nances at foot­ball clubs across the re­gion have been stretched as the health emer­gency forced au­thor­i­ties to sus­pend matches or limit spec­ta­tor num­bers once cham­pi­onships had restarted.</p>


